properties.description:
STAY INFORMED - Green Hills Road (between Kooralbyn and Allandale) bushfire as at 1:00pm Thurs 15 Oct
Bushfire warning level: ADVICE
Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) advises there is a large bushfire in the vicinity of Green Hills Road between Kooralbyn and Allandale.
You need to keep up to date and decide what actions you will take if the situation changes.
Currently, as at 1:00pm Thursday, 15 October, a large bushfire continues to burn in the vicinity of Green Hills Road between Kooralbyn and Allandale. The fire is burning within identified containment lines. 
Aerial assets are providing support to fire crews who are working to strengthen these containment lines. 
Properties are not under direct threat at this time, however residents in isolated properties in the area should remain vigilant. 
People in the area will be affected by smoke, which will reduce visibility and air quality.
Call Triple Zero (000) immediately if you believe you or your property is under threat.
